The paper focuses on developing a novel method for no-reference image quality assessment (NR-IQA) using visual attention mechanisms, robust averaging strategy, and multi-task learning. This involves the use of deep reinforcement learning and back-propagation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) are also possible sub-categories as they relate to image quality assessment and visual perception.
